Class CPoint

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.pyvain.websight.websight.Geometry.CPoint

    java.lang.Comparable<CPoint>

    public final class CPoint
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<CPoint>

    A class that represents a 2-dimensional point with constant integer coordinates.

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors

      CPoint(CPoint p1, CPoint p2, float alpha)
      Creates a new CPoint which is a barycenter of the 2 specified points with specified barycentric coordinates.

      Creates a new CPoint with specified integral cartesian coordinates (x, y).
      CPoint(PolarCoords coords, CPoint origin, float unit)
      Creates a new CPoint with specified polar coordinates (x, y) in a system of specified origin and unit distance.
